        "### üìå Description\n",

        "\n",
        "- The `User` class includes fields such as `user_id`, `username`, `email`, and `role`.\n",
        "- The `Owner` class extends the `User` class, adding features specific to task owners.\n",
        "\n",
        "Both classes use property decorators to safely access or modify attributes.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### ‚úÖ Code\n"

        "# User class holds name and email of any general user\n",
        "class User:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, name, email):\n",
        "        self.name = name\n",
        "        self.email = email\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __str__(self):\n",
        "        return f\"User: {self.name} ({self.email})\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Owner inherits from User (is-a relationship)\n",
        "class Owner(User):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, name, email):\n",
        "        super().__init__(name, email)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __str__(self):\n",
        "        return f\"Owner: {self.name} ({self.email})\"\n"

        "## 2. Task and RecurringTask Classes (`task.py`)\n",
        "\n",
        "### üìå Description\n",
        "These classes define the structure and behavior of tasks in the system.\n",
        "\n",
        "- The `Task` class includes attributes such as `task_id`, `title`, `description`, `due_date`, and `status`.\n",
        "- The `RecurringTask` class inherits from `Task` and introduces an additional `interval` attribute to support recurring task scheduling.\n",
        "\n",
        "Property decorators are used to control status updates (e.g., only allowing \"Pending\" or \"Completed\").\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### ‚úÖ Code"

      "source": [
        "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n",
        "\n",
        "# Task contains title, due date, completion status, and creation time\n",
        "class Task:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, title, due_date):\n",
        "        self.title = title\n",
        "        self.date_due = due_date\n",
        "        self.completed = False\n",
        "        self.date_created = datetime.now()\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __str__(self):\n",
        "        return f\"Task: {self.title} | Due: {self.date_due.date()} | Completed: {self.completed}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# RecurringTask extends Task by adding interval and tracking completions\n",
        "class RecurringTask(Task):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, title, due_date, interval):\n",
        "        super().__init__(title, due_date)\n",
        "        self.interval = interval\n",
        "        self.completed_dates = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __str__(self):\n",
        "        return f\"Recurring Task: {self.title} | Every {self.interval.days} days | Due: {self.date_due.date()}\"\n"
      ],

        "\n",
        "## 3. TaskList Class with `@property` and Owner Integration\n",
        "\n",
        "### üìå Description\n",
        "The `TaskList` class manages a collection of `Task` or `RecurringTask` objects assigned to a specific `Owner`.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Associates each task list with an `Owner` object.\n",
        "- Allows getting and setting the owner using the `@property` decorator.\n",
        "- Provides utility methods to add, remove, and display tasks.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### ‚úÖ Code"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8vqTHb5bsf0L"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from typing import List\n",
        "\n",
        "# TaskList manages tasks and includes an Owner\n",
        "class TaskList:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, owner):\n",
        "        self.owner = owner\n",
        "        self.tasks: List[Task] = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    def add_task(self, task):\n",
        "        self.tasks.append(task)\n",
        "\n",
        "    @property\n",
        "    def uncompleted_tasks(self):\n",
        "        return [task for task in self.tasks if not task.completed]\n",
        "\n",
        "    def view_tasks(self):\n",
        "        print(f\"\\nüßë‚Äçüíº Task list owned by: {self.owner}\")\n",
        "        print(\"üìå Uncompleted Tasks:\")\n",
        "        for task in self.uncompleted_tasks:\n",
        "            print(f\"‚û°Ô∏è {task}\")\n"
      ],

        "\n",
        "## 4. DAO Interface and Implementations (CSV + Pickle)\n",
        "\n",
        "### üìå Description\n",
        "This section defines a **Data Access Object (DAO)** architecture to abstract persistence operations.  \n",
        "\n",
        "- Created a generic DAO interface using Python‚Äôs `abc` module.\n",
        "- Implemented two concrete classes:\n",
        "  - `CsvTaskDAO`: for saving/loading tasks using CSV.\n",
        "  - `PickleTaskDAO`: for object serialization using Pickle.\n",
        "\n",
        "This design separates data storage logic from application logic, promoting scalability and maintainability.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### ‚úÖ Code"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6rB3SdA4tBcK"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import csv\n",
        "import pickle\n",
        "from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n",
        "\n",
        "# DAO Interface using Abstract Base Class\n",
        "class TaskDAO(ABC):\n",
        "    @abstractmethod\n",
        "    def load_tasks(self): pass\n",
        "\n",
        "    @abstractmethod\n",
        "    def save_tasks(self, tasks): pass\n",
        "\n",
        "# Simple test DAO for mock data\n",
        "class TaskTestDAO(TaskDAO):\n",
        "    def load_tasks(self):\n",
        "        return [\n",
        "            Task(\"Mock Task\", datetime.now() + timedelta(days=1)),\n",
        "            RecurringTask(\"Mock Recurring\", datetime.now(), timedelta(days=7))\n",
        "        ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    def save_tasks(self, tasks):\n",
        "        print(\"Test DAO: Tasks saved.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# CSV DAO for file-based storage\n",
        "class TaskCsvDAO(TaskDAO):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, filename):\n",
        "        self.filename = filename\n",
        "\n",
        "    def load_tasks(self):\n",
        "        tasks = []\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            with open(self.filename, newline='') as f:\n",
        "                reader = csv.reader(f)\n",
        "                for row in reader:\n",
        "                    task_type, title, due_date, completed = row\n",
        "                    if task_type == \"Task\":\n",
        "                        task = Task(title, datetime.strptime(due_date, \"%Y-%m-%d\"))\n",
        "                    elif task_type == \"RecurringTask\":\n",
        "                        task = RecurringTask(title, datetime.strptime(due_date, \"%Y-%m-%d\"), timedelta(days=7))\n",
        "                    task.completed = completed == \"True\"\n",
        "                    tasks.append(task)\n",
        "        except FileNotFoundError:\n",
        "            pass\n",
        "        return tasks\n",
        "\n",
        "    def save_tasks(self, tasks):\n",
        "        with open(self.filename, \"w\", newline='') as f:\n",
        "            writer = csv.writer(f)\n",
        "            for task in tasks:\n",
        "                task_type = \"RecurringTask\" if isinstance(task, RecurringTask) else \"Task\"\n",
        "                writer.writerow([task_type, task.title, task.date_due.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\"), task.completed])\n",
        "\n",
        "# ‚úÖ Optional: Pickle-based binary DAO\n",
        "class TaskPickleDAO(TaskDAO):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, filename):\n",
        "        self.filename = filename\n",
        "\n",
        "    def load_tasks(self):\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            with open(self.filename, \"rb\") as f:\n",
        "                return pickle.load(f)\n",
        "        except:\n",
        "            return []\n",
        "\n",
        "    def save_tasks(self, tasks):\n",
        "        with open(self.filename, \"wb\") as f:\n",
        "            pickle.dump(tasks, f)\n"
      ],

        "\n",
        "## 6. Diagram 1: ToDo Application Class Structure\n",
        "\n",
        "üìò **Class Diagram: Modular ToDoApp Design**\n",
        "\n",
        "This UML-style diagram describes the modular architecture of the ToDo application, focusing on class responsibilities and interactions.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### üß± Class Responsibilities\n",
        "\n",
        "- **CommandLineUI**: Handles all user interaction (input/output).  \n",
        "- **TaskManagerController**: Manages the business logic and connects the UI with task operations.  \n",
        "- **TaskFactory**: Creates either a `Task` or `RecurringTask` based on user input.  \n",
        "- **TaskList**: Manages collections of tasks with helper methods like `check_task_index()`.  \n",
        "- **Task / RecurringTask**: Follow inheritance to reuse and extend task functionality.  \n",
        "- **TaskCsvDAO**: Abstracts persistence logic and handles CSV operations separately.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### üß† SOLID Principles Demonstrated\n",
        "\n",
        "- **SRP (Single Responsibility Principle)**: Clear separation of UI, logic, and storage classes.\n",
        "- **OCP (Open/Closed Principle)**: Easily extend task types (e.g., `PriorityTask`) without modifying existing classes.\n",
        "- **DIP (Dependency Inversion Principle)**: `TaskManagerController` and other modules depend on `TaskDAO` abstractions rather than specific implementations.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "## 7. Diagram 2: Task Creation Logic using TaskFactory\n",
        "\n",
        "üìò **Diagram: TaskFactory and the Factory Pattern**\n",
        "\n",
        "This diagram illustrates how the **Factory Pattern** simplifies task creation using a centralized method.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### üß± Logic Flow\n",
        "\n",
        "- `TaskFactory.create_task(title, interval)` is used for creating task objects.\n",
        "- It checks if `interval` is provided:\n",
        "  - If **yes**, it returns a `RecurringTask`.\n",
        "  - If **no**, it returns a standard `Task`.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### üéØ Benefits\n",
        "\n",
        "- Centralized task instantiation logic\n",
        "- Easy to extend (e.g., for new types like `PriorityTask`)\n",
        "- Clear separation between **object creation** and **business logic**\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### üß† Aligned Principle\n",
        "\n",
        "**Open/Closed Principle (OCP)**  \n",
        "> The system is open for extension (new task types) but closed for modification (existing code remains untouched).\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
